                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "There is special provision in dnsmasq to do exactly this, but it's never  made it into libvirt upstream. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Please feel free to push there!\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "from \"man dnsmasq\" NOTES section:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "-------------------------------------------------------------- dhcp-range  may  have  an  interface  name supplied as \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\"interface:<interface-name>\". ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The semantics if this are as follows: For  DHCP, if any other dhcp-range exists _without_ an interface name, then  the interface name is ignored and and  dnsmasq  behaves as  if  the  interface parts did not exist, otherwise DHCP is only provided to  interfaces mentioned in dhcp-range declarations. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "For DNS, if there are  no --interface or --listen-address flags, behaviour is unchanged by the  interface  part. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " If  either  of these flags are present, the interfaces  mentioned in dhcp-ranges are added to the set which get DNS service.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Similarly, enable-tftp may take an interface name, which enables TFTP  only for a particular interface, ignoring --interface or \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "--listen-address flags. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "In addition --tftp-secure and --tftp-unique-root  and --tftp-no-blocksize are ignored for requests from such interfaces. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " (A --tftp-root directive giving a root path and an interface should be  provided too.)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "These   rules   may   seem   odd   at   first   sight,  but   they  allow  a  single  line   of  the  form\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\"dhcp-range=interface:virt0,192.168.0.4,192.168.0.200\" to be added to  dnsmasq configuration which then supplies DHCP and DNS services  to  that interface,  without  affecting  what  services  are  supplied to  other interfaces and irrespective of the existance or lack of  \"interface=<interface>\" lines elsewhere in the dnsmasq configuration. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " \"enable-tftp=virt0\" and \"tftp-root=<root>,virt0\" do the same job for TFTP.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "The  idea is that such a line can be added automatically by libvirt or  equivalent systems, without disturbing any manual configuration.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
